        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 16 at 4:04PM CDT by NWS Lincoln IL</headline>
        <description>At 403 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Bement to near Dalton City to near
Moweaqua. Movement was east at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Decatur, Tuscola, Sullivan, Arcola, Mount Zion, Villa Grove, Arthur,
Moweaqua, Bement, Cerro Gordo, Bethany, Long Creek, Atwood, Blue
Mound, Macon, Lovington, Stonington, Pesotum, Dalton City, and
Hammond.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 57 between mile markers 195 and 224.
Interstate 72 between mile markers 146 and 149.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
